<inglise> I.1. Limits </inglise>
<eesti> I.1. M&auml;&auml;rad </eesti>
<inglise> The sound level of the vehicles referred to in Article 1 of this Directive, when measured under the conditions set out in this Annex, may not exceed the following levels: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi artiklis 1 osutatud s&otilde;idukite m&uuml;ratase, mida m&otilde;&otilde;detakse selles lisas kehtestatud tingimustel, ei tohi &uuml;letada j&auml;rgmisi tasemeid: </eesti>
<inglise> I.2. Measuring instruments </inglise>
<eesti> I. 2. M&otilde;&otilde;tevahendid </eesti>
<inglise> The noise emitted by vehicles shall be measured by means of a sound-level meter of the type described in Publications 179,1 st edition (1965), of the International Electrotechnical Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> S&otilde;idukite tekitatavat m&uuml;ra m&otilde;&otilde;detakse m&uuml;ram&otilde;&otilde;turiga, mida kirjeldatakse Rahvusvahelise Elektrotehnikakomisjoni v&auml;ljaandes nr 179, 1. tr&uuml;kk (1965). </eesti>
<inglise> I.3. Conditions of measurement </inglise>
<eesti> I.3. M&otilde;&otilde;tmistingimused </eesti>
<inglise> Measurements shall be made on unladen vehicles in a sufficiently silent and open area (ambient noise and wind noise at least 10 dB (A) below the noise being measured). </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;&otilde;detakse piisavalt vaikses ja avatud kohas (&uuml;mbritsev m&uuml;ra ja tuule tekitatav m&uuml;ra v&auml;hemalt 10 db (A) v&otilde;rra madalam m&otilde;&otilde;detavast m&uuml;rast) t&uuml;himassiga s&otilde;idukit. </eesti>
<inglise> That area may take the form, for instance, of an open space of 50-metre radius having a central part of at least 20-metre radius which is practically level, surfaced with concrete, asphalt or similar material, and not covered with powdery snow, tall grass, loose soil or ashes. </inglise>
<eesti> See koht v&otilde;ib olla n&auml;iteks 50meetrise raadiusega avatud plats, mille keskosas on v&auml;hemalt 20meetrise raadiusega praktiliselt sile pind, mis on kaetud betooni, asfaldi v&otilde;i samalaadse materjaliga ja millel ei ole lahtist lund, pikka rohtu, lahtist mulda ega tuhka. </eesti>
<inglise> The surface of the test track shall be such as not to cause excessive tyre noise. </inglise>
<eesti> Katseraja pind ei tohi p&otilde;hjustada &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;rast rehvim&uuml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise> This condition applies only to measurement of the noise made by vehicles in motion. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda tingimust kohaldatakse ainult liikuvate s&otilde;idukite tekitatud m&uuml;ra m&otilde;&otilde;tmisel. </eesti>
<inglise> Measurement shall be carried out in fine weather with little wind. </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;&otilde;tmine viiakse l&auml;bi ilusa ilma ja v&auml;hese tuulega. </eesti>
<inglise> No person other than the observer taking the readings from the apparatus may remain near the vehicle or the microphone, as the presence of spectators near either the vehicle or the microphone may considerably affect the readings from the apparatus. </inglise>
<eesti> S&otilde;iduki v&otilde;i mikrofoni juures tohib olla ainult m&otilde;&otilde;diku n&auml;idu lugeja, sest pealtvaatajate juuresolek s&otilde;iduki v&otilde;i mikrofoni juures v&otilde;ib m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt m&otilde;jutada m&otilde;&otilde;diku n&auml;itu. </eesti>
<inglise> Marked fluctuations of the pointer which appear to be unrelated to the characteristics of the general sound level shall be ignored in taking readings. </inglise>
